40|$|The {{effect of}} warm {{prestressing}} (WPS) {{has been investigated}} for the specific material and loading conditions of the central circumferential weld of the reactor pressure vessel of KKS under <b>emergency</b> core <b>cooling.</b> Warm prestressing results in a significant rise of effective fracture toughness. The magnitude of the WPS-effect {{as a function of}} warm prestressing, path of unloading, amount of cooling (e. g. change of yield stress) can be predicted {{on the basis of a}} theoretical model of Chell et al. - Crack initiation can be excluded for <b>emergency</b> core <b>cooling</b> (ECC) -loading and for material conditions beyond end of life for the central circumferential weld of the pressure vessel of KKS...|$|R
