5000|$|In {{a boiling}} water reactor (BWR), the <b>emergency</b> core <b>cooling</b> system (ECCS) injects liquid water into the reactor core from the top. Water vapor {{produced}} from boiling will flow in the opposite direction. Given a high enough flow rate of steam, reversal of the ECCS-injected liquid water occurs.|$|R
